{"title_page": "Adam Ragusea", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name                 = Adam Ragusea\n| logo                 = \n| logo_caption         = \n| image                = \n| image_caption        = \n| birth_name           = \n| birth_date           = March 22, 1982\n| birth_place          = [[Macon, Georgia|Macon]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]\n| death_date           = \n| death_place          = \n| nationality          = American\n| occupation           = Professor of journalism, YouTuber.\n| website              = https://www.adamragusea.com\n| pseudonym            = \n| channel_name         = Adam Ragusea\n| channel_url          = https://www.youtube.com/user/aragusea\n| years_active         = 10\n| genre                = [[Cooking]], [[science journalism]]\n| subscribers          = 741,000\n| subscriber_date      = April 27, 2020\n| views                = 107,824,907\n| view_date            = April 27, 2020\n| catchphrase(s)       = \n| stats_update         = April 27, 2020\n}}\n\n'''Adam Ragusea''' is a [[YouTuber]] who creates videos about food recipes, science, and culinary culture. He was previously a professor of journalism at [[Mercer University]], but quit his job in 2020 after noticing he earned more money from his then amateur YouTube channel.\n== Career ==\n\n=== Journalism ===\nAdam Ragusea was a journalist in residence at Mercer University until February 2020 when he scheduled to retire.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vb7GSuat22E|title=How Adam Ragusea\u2019s journalism background helps him in his YouTube career|date=Feb 12, 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 27, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajc.com/entertainment/dining/food-videos-bring-professor-millions-views/iuB0lADQP5GgzOpZKNoJHJ/|title=Food videos bring Mercer professor millions of views|last=Janani P. Rammohan|first=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|date=|website=ajc|language=English|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref> Ragusea taught introductory and advanced journalism, and media production classes while still a professor at Mercer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ccj.mercer.edu/team/|title=The CCJ Team - Mercer University|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== YouTube ===\nRagusea created his YouTube channel on February 12, 2010, and his first videos were recipes for foods that he made for the intention of sharing with his friends.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.13wmaz.com/video/news/local/youtube-professor-mercer-university-creator-influencer-adam-ragusea/93-adae2e65-356f-49d6-a3a6-94c072e08bb3|title=Former professor quit his job at Mercer to become a full-time YouTube creator|website=WMAZ|access-date=2020-04-28}}</ref> His videos began to garner attention for his \"straight-to-the-point\" style that is influenced by his background in journalism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.13wmaz.com/article/life/people/journalism-professo-turned-youtube-creator/93-12a23947-9aac-403d-8863-66e8d1847f88|title=He was teaching at Mercer when a video he posted on YouTube went viral. Now, he\u2019s a full-time YouTube creator.|website=WMAZ|access-date=2020-04-28}}</ref> In addition to this, he cites [[SpongeBob SquarePants]] as an influence on his style of comedy, claiming that \"it's edgy, but fundamentally it's still just a beam of bright sunshine.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iF7RQVdxCAk|title=The professor that went viral|last=|first=|date=Jul 2, 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ragusea, Adam}}\n\n[[Category:YouTubers]]\n[[Category:American chefs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Adam Ragusea''' is a [[YouTuber]] who creates videos about food recipes, science, and culinary cultu